        <Label fx:id="s" alignment="CENTER" layoutX="536.0" layoutY="91.0" prefHeight="48.0" prefWidth="354.0" text="Instructions">
            <font>
                <Font size="24.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="95.0" layoutY="168.0" prefHeight="73.0" prefWidth="320.0" text="- 10 oz (about 300g) fresh spinach or frozen spinach, thawed and drained" wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="95.0" layoutY="236.0" prefHeight="31.0" prefWidth="279.0" text="- 1 small onion, finely chopped">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="95.0" layoutY="274.0" prefHeight="31.0" prefWidth="300.0" text="- 2-3 green onions, finely chopped">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="486.0" layoutY="179.0" prefHeight="54.0" prefWidth="480.0" text="1. Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C)." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="486.0" layoutY="230.0" prefHeight="74.0" prefWidth="573.0" text="2. In a pan, sauté the chopped onion and green onions in a bit of olive oil until they soften. Add the spinach and cook for a few minutes. Remove from heat and let it cool." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="483.0" layoutY="306.0" prefHeight="54.0" prefWidth="564.0" text="3. In a mixing bowl, combine the spinach mixture, crumbled feta, chopped dill, eggs, salt, and pepper. Mix well." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="483.0" layoutY="359.0" prefHeight="74.0" prefWidth="486.0" text="4. Brush a baking dish with some melted butter or olive oil. Layer half the phyllo sheets in the dish, brushing each layer with more melted butter or olive oil." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Label layoutX="483.0" layoutY="427.0" prefHeight="91.0" prefWidth="582.0" text="5. Spread the spinach mixture evenly over the phyllo layers. Top with the remaining phyllo sheets, again brushing each layer with butter or oil." wrapText="true">
            <font>
                <Font size="15.0" />
            </font>
        </Label>
        <Button fx:id="backButton" layoutX="32.0" layoutY="18.0" mnemonicParsing="false" onAction="#backToJapanese" prefHeight="53.0" prefWidth="104.0" text="Back">
